  <data key="d8">microvascular complications including diabetic neuropathy, retinopathy, nephropathy, and foot disorders || Prevalence of retinopathy, nephropathy, neuropathy, and diabetic foot ulcers were 42.9%, 6.9%, 3.3% and 4.3%, respectively. || DFD were significantly related to new renal events</data>
